import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('x-coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x-coordinates in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['lumosity'], bins=50)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity values in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Lumosity')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    ax.set_xlabel('Terrain Types')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of terrain types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;
